# Trabuddy Color Palette Guidelines

## Overview

Trabuddy uses a nature-inspired color palette consisting of Forest Green (primary), Warm Beige (secondary), and Coral Salmon (accent) colors. This palette creates a trustworthy, natural, and approachable brand experience perfect for travel planning services.

## Primary Color - Forest Green

**Use for**: Brand elements, navigation, main buttons, headers

```css
--color-primary-50: #f8f8f0; /* Very light cream beige - backgrounds */
--color-primary-100: #f0f0e0; /* Light cream beige - card backgrounds */
--color-primary-200: #e6e6cc; /* Light beige - borders, dividers */
--color-primary-300: #d4d4a6; /* Medium beige - disabled states */
--color-primary-400: #c0c080; /* Light forest green - secondary actions */
--color-primary-500: #a8a868; /* Default forest green - main brand color */
--color-primary-600: #9d9d60; /* Medium forest green - hover states */
--color-primary-700: #7a7a40; /* Dark forest green - active states */
--color-primary-800: #565620; /* Very dark forest green - text */
--color-primary-900: #333300; /* Darkest forest green - headings */
```

**Tailwind classes**: `bg-primary-*`, `text-primary-*`, `border-primary-*`

